5 2 New Chapter; Possession of Human Remains for Law Enforcement Purposes. Amend RSA by
6 insertingafterchapter291-Athefollowingnewchapter:
7 CHAPTER291-B
8 POSSESSIONOFHUMANREMAINSFORLAWENFORCEMENTPURPOSES
9 291-B:1 Definitions.
10 Asusedinthischapter:
11 I. “Cadaver canine” means a dog trained to detect the scent of human remains for law
12 enforcementpurposes.
13 II. “Portions of human remains” shall mean identifiable human tissue, bone, or other
14 anatomicalmaterialderivedfromadeceasedindividual.
15 291-B:2 AuthorizationandConsenttoPossessHumanRemainsforLawEnforcementTraining.
16 I. Law enforcement agencies may possess portions of human remains for cadaver canine
17 trainingonlyunderthefollowingconditions:
18 (a) Writtenconsentisobtainedfrom:
19 (1) Thenextofkinorlegalrepresentativeofthedeceased; or
20 (2) The deceased individual, prior to death, through a legally valid document
21 expressing their intent to donate their body or portions thereof for scientific or law enforcement
22 trainingpurposes.
23 (b) The consent explicitly authorizes the use of the remains for training purposes and
24 identifiesthespecificportionstobeused.
25 II. The written consent shall be maintained by both the law enforcement agency and the
26 funeral home or mortuary involved. Such documentation shall be made available for inspection by
27 thelawenforcementagencyorotherregulatoryauthoritiesuponrequest.
28 291-B:3 ConductDuringPossessionofHumanRemains;Return.
29 I. Upon completion of training, all remaining portions of the human remains shall be
30 returnedtoeither:

